  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Letter to Yu Tae-jae
  author: Kim Gu-gyeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    You dwell on the southern shore, I on the northern.
    The games we played in years gone by—still vivid in my dreams.
    Tears from our long parting fall like the Milky Way,
    While my heart, heavy with sorrow, kindles fires within.

    On warm banks, the crabapple blooms redder than silk,
    And on clear days, the riverside willows drift like smoke.

    When shall we clasp hands and meet in joy?
    Two thousand li of longing stretch between our lands.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The Milky Way alludes to the ancient Chinese legend of the Weaver and Cowherd, separated lovers whose tears form the celestial river
  - key: ''
    value: The riverside willows and crabapple flowers evoke the beauty of spring, contrasting poignantly with the speaker's separation from his friend
